{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, many researchers have studied explainable AI technologies to improve the interpretability of machine learning (ML) models.",
    "For instance, for ML behaviors on structured data, researchers have proposed various methods to summarize the contributed features to predictions (Lundberg and Lee, 2017; Fisher et al., 2019) and explain how the models work with data examples (Kim et al., 2016).",
    "Lakkaraju and Bastani (2020) reported misleading explanations on black-box MLs as a cause for users trusting even harmful MLs.",
    "Therefore, considering the characteristics of human design thinking is important to improve the interpretability of AIs for decision-making.",
    "To better understand the aforementioned arguments, Wambsganss et al. (2021) proposed ARGUETUTOR, a chatbot system that provides users with feedback to identify sentences in their documents that require logical improvement."
  ]
}